Paladins are divine warrior-defenders who split from the Cleric tradition during the Sundering Wars.
They formed when clerics swore oaths to defend sacred spaces after temples were desecrated as tactical terrain.
The oath is the institution. It overrides loyalty to any commander or organization.
Combat role is frontline divine melee with advance-and-sanctify doctrine: advance to extend protected ground, sanctify as you go.
Key abilities include divine combat, protective wards, consecration, and shield-warden defense.
The Solar Court's temple-guard auxiliaries are claimed as an earlier ancestor tradition.
Paladins work in partnership with Priests: Paladins advance and create secure ground, Priests sustain healing within it.
Training includes extensive case studies of oath-authority decisions, including cases where Paladins were wrong.
The Templar class synthesizes Paladin advance doctrine with Priest restoration into a single practitioner.
